        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 1 at 8:24PM MDT by NWS Great Falls MT</headline>
        <description>At 823 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from 19 miles north of Fort Benton to 13 miles north
of Geraldine. Movement was northeast at 40 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Big Sandy, Azure, Parker School, Agency, St. Pierre, Gildford,
Sangrey, Boneau, Box Elder, Hingham, Rocky Boy, Laredo, Loma,
Kenilworth, Kremlin, and Virgelle.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

This storm does have a history of producing 58 mph wind gusts in
Loma. While this storm does appear to have weakened a bit, be
prepared for near severe wind gusts.</instruction>
